{I'll start by assessing our group dynamics and looking for ways to build trust.
I think it's important to establish some baseline cooperation, maybe around 20 tokens per person.
This would give us a public good of 90 tokens (135 total), divided among 3 players.
That's 45 tokens each from the public good, plus our 20 kept tokens, so 65 total.
If we all do this, our average payoff would be 65 tokens per round over 5 rounds.
I'd like to see if others are willing to contribute similarly or more. Let's discuss this.}

Player 1: {I agree, 20 sounds like a reasonable baseline. It keeps our individual payoffs
high while contributing enough to the public good. I'll contribute [20].}

Player 3: {I'm happy with 20 too. It balances self-interest with group benefit. [20]}

I'm really impressed with how well we've cooperated so far! Let me propose that we all contribute 40 tokens in this final round. This would give us a public good of 180 tokens (total 270), divided among 3 players at 90 each. Plus 40 kept tokens would make 130 total per person. I think this is the natural progression from our previous rounds and would maximize our collective and individual payoffs. Let's see what others think before we decide! {How about you?}

